[normal]http://www.tni.org/archives/acts_sustainable
[normal]Liberalisation of the energy sector is on the increase on a global scale. During the past decade the world has witnessed a series of catastrophic blackouts, skyrocketing energy tariffs, growing corruption, environmental disasters and the collapse of major corporations. The panel will discuss the promised benefits of liberalisation and present concrete examples of resistance and alternative proposals to market-led energy reforms in South Africa and the world. Sustainable energy for all is possible!
